GAME SIMULATION ENGINE (simulateGame.ts)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Per-game outputs:
  - Home score, away score
  - Quarter-by-quarter score breakdown (distributeToQuarters)
  - Weather condition for the game
  - Full player stat lines for both teams

Stats-first scoring approach:
  - Scoring events (TDs, FGs) generated first from team ratings
  - Player stats derived from scoring events — stats always match the scoreboard
  - Defensive TDs from pick-6s and fumble return TDs added to the defensive
    team's score (not the offensive score)
  - Kicker stats generated from scoring events: FGM = events.fgs,
    XPM = offensive TDs, occasional missed FG attempt adds flavor

Player stat generation covers:
  - QB: completions, attempts, passing yards, TDs, interceptions
  - RB: carries, rushing yards, rushing TDs
  - WR/TE: targets, receptions, receiving yards, receiving TDs
  - DL/LB: tackles, sacks, TFL, forced fumbles
  - DB: tackles, interceptions, pass deflections, defensive TDs (pick-6s)
  - K: FG made, FG attempted, XP made, XP attempted

Game script (scoreDiff influence):
  - Trailing teams pass more (gameScriptPassMod up to 1.20x)
  - Leading teams run more (gameScriptRushMod up to 1.15x)
  - Desperation throws increase INT risk when down 14+

Overtime simulation:
  - Triggers only on tied scores at end of regulation
  - NFL rules: TD on first possession wins; FG gives opponent a chance
  - Both teams fail → sudden death FG decides the game
  - No ties allowed as final result

Weather system (getWeather / weatherMultipliers):
  - Conditions: clear, rain, snow, wind
  - Week-aware (heavier weather more likely in late season weeks)
  - Each condition applies pass multiplier, rush multiplier, score multiplier

Home field advantage:
  - Home team scoring boost applied via baseDrives (+0.5 scoring drives)
  - Away QB accuracy penalty applied (crowd noise simulation)

Depth chart integration:
  - getHealthyByGroup pulls active, non-injured players by position group
  - Cascades to WR2/RB2 automatically when WR1/RB1 are injured
  - Targets distributed proportionally down the depth chart
  - Kicker pulled from K position group

Stat distributions:
  - randomNormal function for realistic bell-curve stat generation
  - Team offense/defense ratings (getTeamRatings) influence output
  - Player individual attributes (attr) pulled from DB per player

MILESTONE SYSTEM (checkMilestones.ts)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Runs after every simulated week and every individual game simulation
- Batches all players who appeared in that week's games (4 DB queries total,
  not per-player — career history, current season, achieved milestones,
  player info all fetched in bulk)
- Combines career_stats_history (past seasons) + current season stats
  to compute live career totals
- Checks 9 career stat categories across 26 thresholds:
  Pass yards, Pass TDs, Rush yards, Rush TDs, Rec yards, Rec TDs,
  Receptions, Sacks, Defensive INTs
- Checks 5 single-season historic thresholds (keyed per season, per player):
  5,000 pass yards, 50 pass TDs, 2,000 rush yards, 2,000 rec yards, 20 rush TDs
- Each milestone stored in player_milestones with PRIMARY KEY
  (player_id, milestone_key) — fires exactly once, never duplicates
- Milestone events written to news_events under category 'milestones'
  with player_id and team_id for news feed filtering

PLAYER LIFECYCLE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Contracts:
  - Each player has salary (AAV), years remaining, signing bonus / dead cap
  - Salary cap enforced on signings, extensions, and restructures
  - Dead cap tracked on release

Injuries:
